What you need to know:

Thousands have been left homeless and hundreds of thousands others are at risk of being displaced by flooding.Residents are now living in fear after researchers said the situation may not get better any time soon.According to WRA, it was in May 2020 that Lake Naivasha reached its highest level since 1932.On the other hand, Lake Nakuru saw a significant rise of 77 per cent in the same period.